#!"C:\Program Files\Universal\Python36\python.exe" # -- # Origins: Stonebranch # Author: Nils Buer # Date: 13-SEPT-2018 # # Requires Universal Agent for Windows # # Copyright (c) Stonebranch, 2018. All rights reserved. # # Purpose: import SAP calendar to UC using a CVS file # # Version History: 0.9 NBU 13-SEPT-2018 Created Script # 1.0 NBU 17-SEPT-2018 version support # 1.1 NBU 21-SEPT-2018 bug fixed # 1.2 NBU 24-OCT-2018 Import all Calendar added # # -- version = "1.2"
import logging import sys import csv import time import datetime import os import subprocess
# -- logging settings DEBUG, INFO, WARNING, ERROR, CRITICAL
logging.basicConfig(level=logging.${ops_var_loglevel}, format=' %(asctime)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s')
# -- Main Logic Function def main(): script_setup() # -- Import Required Modules, Setup Logging Format, Set Variables
def script_setup(): logging.info("Settings ") logging.info(r"SAP Calendar export UT Version: " + str(version)) logging.info(r"USAP started with loglevel: ${ops_var_level} ") logging.info(r"sapnwrfc.ini destination: ${ops_var_sapnwrfcdir} ") logging.info(r"SAP destination: ${ops_var_dest} ") logging.info(r"SAP ASHOST: ${ops_var_ashost} ") logging.info(r"SAP SID: ${ops_var_sid} ") logging.info(r"SAP Client: ${ops_var_client} ") logging.info(r"SAP User: ${_credentialUser("${ops_var_sapcred}")} ") logging.info(r"SAP Password: ${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_sapcred}")} ") logging.info(r"Controller url: ${ops_var_opscliurl} ")
if "${ops_var_importall}" == "Yes" : import_all_calendar() else : read_csv()
def import_all_calendar(): # extract all calendars without details from sap and convert it into a python dict # than extract for each calendar the factory and holiday calendar details
os.chdir(r"${ops_var_sapnwrfcdir}") if "${ops_var_ashost}" == "" : # running Stonebranch SAP Connector USAP with destination connection with sapnrfc.ini logging.info("using destination server connection ") try: process = subprocess.check_output(['usap','-dest','${ops_var_dest}','-client','${ops_var_client}','-userid','${_credentialUser("${ops_var_sapcred}")}','-pwd','${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_sapcred}")}','-level','${ops_var_level}','-lang','english','-D','calendars','-calendartype','fact','-calendarid','%','-details','no']) except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e: print (e.output) logging.error("Error Code: " + str(e.returncode)) exit(1) else: # running Stonebranch SAP Connector USAP with sap connection from controller logging.info("using application server connection ") try: process = subprocess.check_output(['usap','-ashost','${ops_var_ashost}','-client','${ops_var_client}','-sysnr','${ops_var_sysnr}','-userid','${_credentialUser("${ops_var_sapcred}")}','-pwd','${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_sapcred}")}','-level','${ops_var_level}','-lang','english','-D','calendars','-calendartype','fact','-calendarid','%','-details','no']) except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e: print (e.output) logging.error("Error Code: " + str(e.returncode)) exit(1) out = process.decode(encoding='utf-8', errors='ignore') fieldnames = ['','ID','VJAH','BJAH','M','D','M','D','F','S','S','F','HO','BASIS','A','CRUSR','CRDAT','CRTIME','I','AKTV','AKTB','DESCRIPTION'] reader = csv.DictReader(out.split('\n'), delimiter='|', fieldnames=fieldnames) ## skip first 6 rows next(reader) next(reader) next(reader) next(reader) next(reader) next(reader) line_count = 0 for row in reader: # print('\t'.join(row)) fact_calid = row["ID"] hol_calid = row["HO"] bjah = row["BJAH"] DESCRIPTION = row["DESCRIPTION"] # logging.info("Factory Calendar ID {} and holiday calendar {} and valid until {} ".format(DESCRIPTION,fact_calid,hol_calid,bjah)) if bjah is not None : year = time.strftime("%Y") if int(bjah) >= int(year) : export_calendar(fact_calid,hol_calid) import_calendar(fact_calid,hol_calid) logging.info("Imported Calendar: {} with Factory Calendar ID {} and holiday calendar {} and valid until {} ".format(DESCRIPTION,fact_calid,hol_calid,bjah)) line_count += 1 logging.info("{} Calendar have been imported from SAP".format(line_count))
def export_calendar(fact_calid,hol_calid): logging.info("Export Process from SAP started ") logging.info("exporting factory calendar with ID: " + str(fact_calid)) logging.info("exporting holiday calendar with ID: " + str(hol_calid))
if "${ops_var_ashost}" == "" : # running Stonebranch SAP Connector USAP with destination connection with sapnrfc.ini logging.info("using application server connection ") if hol_calid == "" : logging.info("no holiday calendar provided ") else: cmd_hol_cal = """usap -dest ${ops_var_dest} -client ${ops_var_client} -userid ${_credentialUser("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -pwd ${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -level ${ops_var_level} -lang english -D calendars -calendartype hol -calendarid {hol_calid} -details yes > ${ops_var_sapout}sap_hol_cal#${ops_var_sid}_${ops_var_client}_{hol_calid}.txt""".format(hol_calid=hol_calid) os.system(cmd_hol_cal) cmd_fact_cal = """usap -dest ${ops_var_dest} -client ${ops_var_client} -userid ${_credentialUser("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -pwd ${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -level ${ops_var_level} -lang english -D calendars -calendartype fact -calendarid {fact_calid} -details yes > ${ops_var_sapout}sap_fact_cal#${ops_var_sid}_${ops_var_client}_{fact_calid}.txt""".format(fact_calid=fact_calid) os.system(cmd_fact_cal)
else: # running Stonebranch SAP Connector USAP with sap connection from controller logging.info("using destination server connection ") if hol_calid == "" : logging.info("no holiday calendar provided ") else: cmd_hol_cal = """usap -ashost ${ops_var_ashost} -client ${ops_var_client} -sysnr ${ops_var_sysnr} -userid ${_credentialUser("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -pwd ${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -level ${ops_var_level} -lang english -D calendars -calendartype hol -calendarid {hol_calid} -details yes > ${ops_var_sapout}sap_hol_cal#${ops_var_sid}_${ops_var_client}_{hol_calid}.txt""".format(hol_calid=hol_calid) os.system(cmd_hol_cal) cmd_fact_cal = """usap -ashost ${ops_var_ashost} -client ${ops_var_client} -sysnr ${ops_var_sysnr} -userid ${_credentialUser("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -pwd ${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_sapcred}")} -level ${ops_var_level} -lang english -D calendars -calendartype fact -calendarid {fact_calid} -details yes > ${ops_var_sapout}sap_fact_cal#${ops_var_sid}_${ops_var_client}_{fact_calid}.txt""".format(fact_calid=fact_calid) os.system(cmd_fact_cal)
logging.info("Export Process from SAP finished ")
def import_calendar(fact_calid,hol_calid):
logging.info("Import Process to Universal Controller ${ops_var_opscliurl} started ") logging.info("importing factory calendar with ID: " + str(fact_calid) ) logging.info("importing holiday calendar with ID: " + str(hol_calid) )
# ## Runing Conversion Tool (Note put workdays parameter before holiday parameter) if hol_calid == "" : cmd = """"${ops_var_javabin}java" -jar ${ops_var_pathToJar} --cliType=SAP --cliUser=${_credentialUser("${ops_var_xctcred}")} --cliPassword=${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_xctcred}")} --cliCalendarWorkDays=${ops_var_sapout}sap_fact_cal#${ops_var_sid}_${ops_var_client}_{fact_calid}.txt --cliModifyExisting=true""".format(fact_calid=fact_calid) else: cmd = """"${ops_var_javabin}java" -jar ${ops_var_pathToJar} --cliType=SAP --cliUser=${_credentialUser("${ops_var_xctcred}")} --cliPassword=${_credentialPwd("${ops_var_xctcred}")} --cliCalendarWorkDays=${ops_var_sapout}sap_fact_cal#${ops_var_sid}_${ops_var_client}_{fact_calid}.txt --cliCalendarFreeDays=${ops_var_sapout}sap_hol_cal#${ops_var_sid}_${ops_var_client}_{hol_calid}.txt --cliModifyExisting=true""".format(fact_calid=fact_calid,hol_calid=hol_calid) os.system(cmd) try: subprocess.check_output(cmd, shell=True) except subprocess.CalledProcessError as e: logging.error("Error Code: " + str(e.returncode)) exit(1) logging.info("Import Process to Universal Controller finished ")
def read_csv(): fieldnames = ['ID','HO'] reader = csv.DictReader(open(r'${_scriptPath('${ops_var_script}')}'), delimiter=',', fieldnames=fieldnames) ## skip first row next(reader) line_count = 0 for row in reader: fact_calid = row["ID"] hol_calid = row["HO"] logging.info("Processing Factory Calendar ID {} and holiday calendar {} ".format(fact_calid,hol_calid)) export_calendar(fact_calid,hol_calid) import_calendar(fact_calid,hol_calid) line_count += 1 logging.info("{} Calendar have been imported from SAP".format(line_count))
### Main # -- Execute main()
